qTextArr:
["I know the real
reason why Robert won't marry me, Jake. It's just come to me. They've
sent it to me in a vision in the Caf  Select. Isn't it mystic? Some day
they'll put a tablet up. Like at Lourdes. Do you want to hear, Robert?
I'll tell you. It's so simple. I wonder why I never thought about it.
Why, you see, Robert's always wanted to have a mistress, and if he
doesn't marry me, why, then he's had one. She was his mistress for over
two years. See how it is? And if he marries me, like he's always
promised he would, that would be the end of all the romance. Don't you
think that's bright of me to figure that out? It's true, too. Look at
him and see if it's not. Where are you going, Jake?"]

["Wonderful nigger. Looked like Tiger Flowers, only four times as big.

white boy hit him. Then he knocked white boy cold. Then everybody
commenced to throw chairs. Nigger went home with us in our car. Couldn't
get his clothes. Wore my coat. Remember the whole thing now. Big
sporting evening."]

qTextArr: ["Oh, I am. I'm frightfully fit. I've done nothing but walk. Walk all day\nlong. One drink a day with my mother at tea."]
qText:
Oh, I am. I'm frightfully fit. I've done nothing but walk. Walk all day
long. One drink a day with my mother at tea.
speaker: Mike Campbell

qTextArr: ["It's good to see you, Jake,", "I'm a little tight you\nknow. Amazing, isn't it? Did you see my nose?"]
qText:
It's good to see you, Jake, I'm a little tight you
know. Amazing, isn't it? Did you see my nose?
speaker: Mike Campbell

qTextArr: ["An old lady's bags did that,", 'I reached up to help her with\nthem and they fell on me.']
qText:
An old lady's bags did that, I reached up to help her with
them and they fell on me.
speaker: Mike Campbell

qTextArr: ['An old lady,', "Her bags _fell_ on me. Let's go in and see\nBrett. I say, she is a piece."]
qText:
An old lady, Her bags _fell_ on me. Let's go in and see
Brett. I say, she is a piece.
speaker: Mike Campbell

qTextArr: ['You _are_ a lovely lady, Brett. Where did\nyou get that hat?']
qText:
You _are_ a lovely lady, Brett. Where did
you get that hat?
speaker: Mike Campbell

qTextArr: ["Chap bought it for me. Don't you like it?"]
qText: Chap bought it for me. Don't you like it?
speaker: Brett Ashley

qTextArr: ["It's a dreadful hat. Do get a good hat."]
qText: It's a dreadful hat. Do get a good hat.
speaker: Mike Campbell

qTextArr: ["Oh, we've so much money now,", "I say, haven't you met Bill\nyet? You _are_ a lovely host, Jake."]
qText:
Oh, we've so much money now, I say, haven't you met Bill
yet? You _are_ a lovely host, Jake.
speaker: Brett Ashley
menEnts: [[['Mike Campbell', 'Brett Ashley']], [['Mike Campbell'], ['Bill Gorton'], ['Jake Barnes'], ['Jake Barnes']]]

qTextArr: ['This is Bill Gorton. This drunkard is Mike\nCampbell. Mr. Campbell is an undischarged bankrupt.']
qText:
This is Bill Gorton. This drunkard is Mike
Campbell. Mr. Campbell is an undischarged bankrupt.
speaker: Brett Ashley

qTextArr: ["Aren't I, though? You know I met my ex-partner yesterday in London.\nChap who did me in."]
qText:
Aren't I, though? You know I met my ex-partner yesterday in London.
Chap who did me in.
speaker: Mike Campbell

qText: What did he say?
speaker: Brett Ashley

qTextArr: ["Bought me a drink. I thought I might as well take it. I say, Brett, you\n_are_ a lovely piece. Don't you think she's beautiful?"]
qText:
Bought me a drink. I thought I might as well take it. I say, Brett, you
_are_ a lovely piece. Don't you think she's beautiful?
speaker: Mike Campbell

qText: Beautiful. With this nose?
speaker: Brett Ashley

qTextArr: ["It's a lovely nose. Go on, point it at me. Isn't she a lovely piece?"]
qText: It's a lovely nose. Go on, point it at me. Isn't she a lovely piece?
speaker: Mike Campbell

qTextArr: ["Couldn't we have kept the man in Scotland?"]
qText: Couldn't we have kept the man in Scotland?
speaker: Brett Ashley

qTextArr: ["I say, Brett, let's turn in early."]
qText: I say, Brett, let's turn in early.
speaker: Mike Campbell

qTextArr: ["Don't be indecent, Michael. Remember there are ladies at this bar."]
qText: Don't be indecent, Michael. Remember there are ladies at this bar.
speaker: Brett Ashley

qTextArr: ["Isn't she a lovely piece? Don't you think so, Jake?"]
qText: Isn't she a lovely piece? Don't you think so, Jake?
speaker: Mike Campbell

qText: There's a fight to-night, Like to go?
speaker: Bill Gorton

qText: Fight, Who's fighting?
speaker: Mike Campbell

qText: Ledoux and somebody.
speaker: Bill Gorton

qTextArr: ["He's very good, Ledoux,", "I'd like to see it, rather", "but I can't go. I had a\ndate with this thing here. I say, Brett, do get a new hat."]
qText:
He's very good, Ledoux, I'd like to see it, rather but I can't go. I had a
date with this thing here. I say, Brett, do get a new hat.
speaker: Mike Campbell

qTextArr: ["You two run along to the fight. I'll have to be taking Mr.\nCampbell home directly."]
qText:
You two run along to the fight. I'll have to be taking Mr.
Campbell home directly.
speaker: Brett Ashley

qTextArr: ["I'm not tight,", 'Perhaps just a little. I say, Brett, you\nare a lovely piece.']
qText:
I'm not tight, Perhaps just a little. I say, Brett, you
are a lovely piece.
speaker: Mike Campbell

qTextArr: ['Go on to the fight,', "Mr. Campbell's getting difficult.\nWhat are these outbursts of affection, Michael?"]
qText:
Go on to the fight, Mr. Campbell's getting difficult.
What are these outbursts of affection, Michael?
speaker: Brett Ashley

qTextArr: ['I say, you are a lovely piece.']
qText: I say, you are a lovely piece.
speaker: Mike Campbell

qText: I'm sorry I can't go,
speaker: Mike Campbell

qTextArr: ['Do you want to go to the fight?']
qText: Do you want to go to the fight?
speaker: Jake Barnes

qText: Sure, If we don't have to walk.
speaker: Bill Gorton

qTextArr: ['Mike was pretty excited about his girl friend,']
qText: Mike was pretty excited about his girl friend,
speaker: Jake Barnes

qTextArr: ['Well,', "You can't blame him such a hell of a lot."]
qText: Well, You can't blame him such a hell of a lot.
speaker: Bill Gorton

qText: Hello, darling.
speaker: Brett Ashley

qTextArr: ['Hello, Jake,', 'I understand I was tight last night.']
qText: Hello, Jake, I understand I was tight last night.
speaker: Mike Campbell

qText: Weren't you, though, Disgraceful business.
speaker: Brett Ashley

qTextArr: ['Look,', 'when do you go down to Spain? Would you mind if we\ncame down with you?']
qText:
Look, when do you go down to Spain? Would you mind if we
came down with you?
speaker: Mike Campbell

qText: It would be grand.
speaker: Jake Barnes

qTextArr: ["You wouldn't mind, really? I've been at Pamplona, you know. Brett's mad\nto go. You're sure we wouldn't just be a bloody nuisance?"]
qText:
You wouldn't mind, really? I've been at Pamplona, you know. Brett's mad
to go. You're sure we wouldn't just be a bloody nuisance?
speaker: Mike Campbell
menEnts: [[['Jake Barnes'], ['Jake Barnes'], ['Brett Ashley'], ['Jake Barnes'], ['Mike Campbell', 'Brett Ashley']]]

qText: Don't talk like a fool.
speaker: Jake Barnes

qTextArr: ["I'm a little tight, you know. I wouldn't ask you like this if I\nweren't. You're sure you don't mind?"]
qText:
I'm a little tight, you know. I wouldn't ask you like this if I
weren't. You're sure you don't mind?
speaker: Mike Campbell

qTextArr: ['Oh, shut up, Michael,', "How can the man say he'd mind now?\nI'll ask him later."]
qText:
Oh, shut up, Michael, How can the man say he'd mind now?
I'll ask him later.
speaker: Brett Ashley

qText: But you don't mind, do you?
speaker: Mike Campbell

qTextArr: ["Don't ask that again unless you want to make me sore. Bill and I go\ndown on the morning of the 25th."]
qText:
Don't ask that again unless you want to make me sore. Bill and I go
down on the morning of the 25th.
speaker: Jake Barnes

qText: By the way, where is Bill?
speaker: Brett Ashley

qTextArr: ["He's out at Chantilly dining with some people."]
qText: He's out at Chantilly dining with some people.
speaker: Jake Barnes

qText: He's a good chap.
speaker: Brett Ashley

qText: Splendid chap, He is, you know.
speaker: Mike Campbell

qText: You don't remember him,
speaker: Brett Ashley

qTextArr: ["I do. Remember him perfectly. Look, Jake, we'll come down the night of\nthe 25th. Brett can't get up in the morning."]
qText:
I do. Remember him perfectly. Look, Jake, we'll come down the night of
the 25th. Brett can't get up in the morning.
speaker: Mike Campbell

qText: Indeed not!
speaker: Brett Ashley

qTextArr: ["If our money comes and you're sure you don't mind."]
qText: If our money comes and you're sure you don't mind.
speaker: Mike Campbell

qTextArr: ["It will come, all right. I'll see to that."]
qText: It will come, all right. I'll see to that.
speaker: Brett Ashley

qTextArr: ['Tell me what tackle to send for.']
qText: Tell me what tackle to send for.
speaker: Mike Campbell

qTextArr: ['Get two or three rods with reels, and lines, and some flies.']
qText: Get two or three rods with reels, and lines, and some flies.
speaker: Jake Barnes

qText: I won't fish,
speaker: Brett Ashley

qTextArr: ["Get two rods, then, and Bill won't have to buy one."]
qText: Get two rods, then, and Bill won't have to buy one.
speaker: Jake Barnes

qTextArr: ['Right,', "I'll send a wire to the keeper."]
qText: Right, I'll send a wire to the keeper.
speaker: Mike Campbell

qTextArr: ["Won't it be splendid,", 'Spain! We _will_ have fun.']
qText: Won't it be splendid, Spain! We _will_ have fun.
speaker: Brett Ashley

qText: The 25th. When is that?
speaker: Brett Ashley

qText: Saturday.
speaker: Jake Barnes

qText: We _will_ have to get ready.
speaker: Brett Ashley

qText: I say, I'm going to the barber's.
speaker: Mike Campbell

qTextArr: ['I must bathe,', 'Walk up to the hotel with me, Jake. Be a\ngood chap.']
qText:
I must bathe, Walk up to the hotel with me, Jake. Be a
good chap.
speaker: Brett Ashley

qTextArr: ['We _have_ got the loveliest hotel,', "I think it's a\nbrothel!"]
qText:
We _have_ got the loveliest hotel, I think it's a
brothel!
speaker: Mike Campbell

qTextArr: ['We left our bags here at the Dingo when we got in, and they asked us at\nthis hotel if we wanted a room for the afternoon only. Seemed\nfrightfully pleased we were going to stay all night.']
qText:
We left our bags here at the Dingo when we got in, and they asked us at
this hotel if we wanted a room for the afternoon only. Seemed
frightfully pleased we were going to stay all night.
speaker: Brett Ashley
menEnts: [[['Mike Campbell', 'Brett Ashley'], ['Mike Campbell', 'Brett Ashley'], ['Mike Campbell', 'Brett Ashley'], ['Mike Campbell', 'Brett Ashley'], ['Mike Campbell', 'Brett Ashley']]]

qTextArr: ["_I_ believe it's a brothel,", 'And _I_ should know.']
qText: _I_ believe it's a brothel, And _I_ should know.
speaker: Mike Campbell

qTextArr: ['Oh, shut it and go and get your hair cut.']
qText: Oh, shut it and go and get your hair cut.
speaker: Brett Ashley

qTextArr: ['I needed that,', "I haven't seen you since I've been back,"]
qText: I needed that, I haven't seen you since I've been back,
speaker: Brett Ashley

qText: No.
speaker: Jake Barnes

qText: How _are_ you, Jake?
speaker: Brett Ashley

qText: Fine.
speaker: Jake Barnes

qTextArr: ['I say,', 'is Robert Cohn going on this\ntrip?']
qText:
I say, is Robert Cohn going on this
trip?
speaker: Brett Ashley

qText: Yes. Why?
speaker: Jake Barnes

qTextArr: ["Don't you think it will be a bit rough on him?"]
qText: Don't you think it will be a bit rough on him?
speaker: Brett Ashley

qText: Why should it?
speaker: Jake Barnes

qTextArr: ['Who did you think I went down to San Sebastian with?']
qText: Who did you think I went down to San Sebastian with?
speaker: Brett Ashley

qText: Congratulations,
speaker: Jake Barnes

qText: What did you say that for?
speaker: Brett Ashley

qTextArr: ["I don't know. What would you like me to say?"]
qText: I don't know. What would you like me to say?
speaker: Jake Barnes

qTextArr: ['He behaved rather well, too. He gets a little dull.']
qText: He behaved rather well, too. He gets a little dull.
speaker: Brett Ashley

qText: Does he?
speaker: Jake Barnes

qTextArr: ['I rather thought it would be good for him.']
qText: I rather thought it would be good for him.
speaker: Brett Ashley

qText: You might take up social service.
speaker: Jake Barnes

qText: Don't be nasty.
speaker: Brett Ashley

qText: I won't.
speaker: Jake Barnes

qText: Didn't you really know?
speaker: Brett Ashley

qTextArr: ['No,', "I guess I didn't think about it."]
qText: No, I guess I didn't think about it.
speaker: Jake Barnes

qTextArr: ['Do you think it will be too rough on him?']
qText: Do you think it will be too rough on him?
speaker: Brett Ashley

qTextArr: ["That's up to him,", "Tell him you're coming. He can always not\ncome."]
qText:
That's up to him, Tell him you're coming. He can always not
come.
speaker: Jake Barnes

qTextArr: ["I'll write him and give him a chance to pull out of it."]
qText: I'll write him and give him a chance to pull out of it.
speaker: Brett Ashley

qText: Did you hear from Cohn?
speaker: Jake Barnes

qText: Rather. He's keen about it.
speaker: Brett Ashley

qText: My God!
speaker: Jake Barnes

qTextArr: ['I thought it was rather odd myself.']
qText: I thought it was rather odd myself.
speaker: Brett Ashley

qTextArr: ["Says he can't wait to see me."]
qText: Says he can't wait to see me.
speaker: Brett Ashley

qText: Does he think you're coming alone?
speaker: Jake Barnes

qTextArr: ['No. I told him we were all coming down together. Michael and all.']
qText: No. I told him we were all coming down together. Michael and all.
speaker: Brett Ashley

qText: He's wonderful.
speaker: Jake Barnes

qText: Isn't he?
speaker: Brett Ashley

qText: Nothing until the fifth.
speaker: The Conductor

qText: What's this?
speaker: Jake Barnes

qTextArr: ["They're all reserved,", 'There will be a\nfifth service at three-thirty.']
qText:
They're all reserved, There will be a
fifth service at three-thirty.
speaker: The Conductor

qText: This is serious,
speaker: Jake Barnes

qText: Give him ten francs.
speaker: Bill Gorton

qTextArr: ['Here,', 'We want to eat in the first service.']
qText: Here, We want to eat in the first service.
speaker: Jake Barnes

qTextArr: ['Thank you,', 'I would advise you gentlemen to get some\nsandwiches. All the places for the first four services were reserved at\nthe office of the company.']
qText:
Thank you, I would advise you gentlemen to get some
sandwiches. All the places for the first four services were reserved at
the office of the company.
speaker: The Conductor

You'll go a long way, brother, I suppose
if I'd given you five francs you would have advised us to jump off the
train.
speaker: Bill Gorton
menEnts: [[['The Conductor'], ['The Conductor']], [['The Conductor'], ['The Conductor'], ['Jake Barnes', 'Bill Gorton']]]

qText: _Comment?_
speaker: The Conductor

qText:
Go to hell! Get the sandwiches made and a bottle of wine.
You tell him, Jake.
speaker: Bill Gorton

qTextArr: ['And send it up to the next car.']
qText: And send it up to the next car.
speaker: Jake Barnes

qTextArr: ["I suppose you're Americans, aren't you?", 'Having a good\ntrip?']
qText:
I suppose you're Americans, aren't you? Having a good
trip?
speaker: The Man

qText: Wonderful,
speaker: Bill Gorton

qTextArr: ["That's what you want to do. Travel while you're young. Mother and I\nalways wanted to get over, but we had to wait a while."]
qText:
That's what you want to do. Travel while you're young. Mother and I
always wanted to get over, but we had to wait a while.
speaker: The Man
menEnts: [[['Jake Barnes', 'Bill Gorton'], ['Jake Barnes', 'Bill Gorton'], ['The Wife', 'The Man']]]

qTextArr: ["You could have come over ten years ago, if you'd wanted to,", 'What you always said was:', "I will say we've\nseen a good deal, take it one way and another."]
qText:
You could have come over ten years ago, if you'd wanted to, What you always said was: I will say we've
seen a good deal, take it one way and another.
speaker: The Wife

qTextArr: ["Say, there's plenty of Americans on this train,", "They've got seven cars of them from Dayton, Ohio. They've been on a\npilgrimage to Rome, and now they're going down to Biarritz and Lourdes."]
qText:
Say, there's plenty of Americans on this train, They've got seven cars of them from Dayton, Ohio. They've been on a
pilgrimage to Rome, and now they're going down to Biarritz and Lourdes.
speaker: The Man

qTextArr: ["So, that's what they are. Pilgrims. Goddam Puritans,"]
qText: So, that's what they are. Pilgrims. Goddam Puritans,
speaker: Bill Gorton

qTextArr: ['What part of the States you boys from?']
qText: What part of the States you boys from?
speaker: The Man

qText: Kansas City, He's from Chicago.
speaker: Jake Barnes

qText: You both going to Biarritz?
speaker: The Man

qText: No. We're going fishing in Spain.
speaker: Jake Barnes

qTextArr: ["Well, I never cared for it, myself. There's plenty that do out where I\ncome from, though. We got some of the best fishing in the State of\nMontana. I've been out with the boys, but I never cared for it any."]
qText:
Well, I never cared for it, myself. There's plenty that do out where I
come from, though. We got some of the best fishing in the State of
Montana. I've been out with the boys, but I never cared for it any.
speaker: The Man

qTextArr: ['Mighty little fishing you did on them trips,']
qText: Mighty little fishing you did on them trips,
speaker: The Wife

qTextArr: ["You know how the ladies are. If there's a jug goes along, or a case of\nbeer, they think it's hell and damnation."]
qText:
You know how the ladies are. If there's a jug goes along, or a case of
beer, they think it's hell and damnation.
speaker: The Man

qTextArr: ["That's the way men are,", "I voted against prohibition to please him, and because\nI like a little beer in the house, and then he talks that way. It's a\nwonder they ever find any one to marry them."]
qText:
That's the way men are, I voted against prohibition to please him, and because
I like a little beer in the house, and then he talks that way. It's a
wonder they ever find any one to marry them.
speaker: The Wife

qTextArr: ['Say,', 'do you know that gang of Pilgrim Fathers have\ncornered the dining-car until half past three this afternoon?']
qText:
Say, do you know that gang of Pilgrim Fathers have
cornered the dining-car until half past three this afternoon?
speaker: Bill Gorton

qTextArr: ["How do you mean? They can't do a thing like that."]
qText: How do you mean? They can't do a thing like that.
speaker: The Man

qText: You try and get seats.
speaker: Bill Gorton

qTextArr: ['Well, mother, it looks as though we better go back and get another\nbreakfast.']
qText:
Well, mother, it looks as though we better go back and get another
breakfast.
speaker: The Man

qTextArr: ['Will you boys keep an eye on our things? Come on, Hubert.']
qText: Will you boys keep an eye on our things? Come on, Hubert.
speaker: The Wife

qText: You're going to work to-day,
speaker: Jake Barnes

qText: They start now, at ten-thirty.
speaker: A Waiter

qText: When do we eat?
speaker: Jake Barnes

qText: Huh! When do I eat?
speaker: A Waiter

qTextArr: ["I'll get the plates,", 'or bring them with you.']
qText: I'll get the plates, or bring them with you.
speaker: A Waiter

qText: Is there good swimming in Biarritz?
speaker: Hubert

qTextArr: ["That boy's just crazy till he can get in the water,", "It's pretty hard on youngsters travelling."]
qText: That boy's just crazy till he can get in the water, It's pretty hard on youngsters travelling.
speaker: The Wife

qTextArr: ["There's good swimming,", "But it's dangerous when it's rough."]
qText: There's good swimming, But it's dangerous when it's rough.
speaker: Jake Barnes

qText: Did you get a meal?
speaker: Bill Gorton

qTextArr: ['We sure did. We set right there when they started to come in, and they\nmust have just thought we were in the party. One of the waiters said\nsomething to us in French, and then they just sent three of them back.']
qText:
We sure did. We set right there when they started to come in, and they
must have just thought we were in the party. One of the waiters said
something to us in French, and then they just sent three of them back.
speaker: The Wife
menEnts: [[['Hubert', 'The Man', 'The Wife'], ['Hubert', 'The Man', 'The Wife'], ['Hubert', 'The Man', 'The Wife'], ['Hubert', 'The Man', 'The Wife']]]

qTextArr: ['They thought we were snappers, all right,', "It certainly\nshows you the power of the Catholic Church. It's a pity you boys ain't\nCatholics. You could get a meal, then, all right."]
qText:
They thought we were snappers, all right, It certainly
shows you the power of the Catholic Church. It's a pity you boys ain't
Catholics. You could get a meal, then, all right.
speaker: The Man
menEnts: [[['Hubert', 'The Man', 'The Wife']], [['Jake Barnes', 'Bill Gorton'], ['Jake Barnes', 'Bill Gorton']]]

qTextArr: ['I am,', "That's what makes me so sore."]
qText: I am, That's what makes me so sore.
speaker: Jake Barnes

qTextArr: ['When do us Protestants get a chance to eat, father?']
qText: When do us Protestants get a chance to eat, father?
speaker: Bill Gorton

qTextArr: ["I don't know anything about it. Haven't you got tickets?"]
qText: I don't know anything about it. Haven't you got tickets?
speaker: A Priest

qTextArr: ["It's enough to make a man join the Klan,"]
qText: It's enough to make a man join the Klan,
speaker: Bill Gorton

qTextArr: ['Well, I hope you have lots of luck,']
qText: Well, I hope you have lots of luck,
speaker: The Man

qText: Be careful about those bull-fights.
speaker: The Wife

qText: Maybe we'll see you at Biarritz,
speaker: Hubert

qText: Hello, Jake. Have a good trip?
speaker: Robert Cohn

qText: Fine, This is Bill Gorton.
speaker: Jake Barnes

qText: How are you?
speaker: Bill Gorton

qText: Come on, I've got a cab.
speaker: Robert Cohn

qTextArr: ["We'll go up to my hotel. It's all right. It's quite nice."]
qText: We'll go up to my hotel. It's all right. It's quite nice.
speaker: Robert Cohn

qTextArr: ["I'm awfully glad to meet you,", "I've heard so much\nabout you from Jake and I've read your books. Did you get my line,\nJake?"]

I'm awfully glad to meet you, I've heard so much
about you from Jake and I've read your books. Did you get my line,
Jake?

menEnts: [[['Bill Gorton']], [['Bill Gorton'], ['Jake Barnes'], ['Bill Gorton'], ['Jake Barnes'], ['Jake Barnes']]]

qTextArr: ["What's the matter with the old one?"]
qText: What's the matter with the old one?
speaker: Jake Barnes

speaker: Jake Barnes

speaker: The Carabineer

speaker: The Carabineer

qText: Well, Brett and Mike ought to get in to-night.

qText: I'm not sure they'll come,
speaker: Robert Cohn

qText: Why not? Of course they'll come.

qText: They're always late,
speaker: Jake Barnes

qText: I rather think they're not coming,
speaker: Robert Cohn

qText: I'll bet you fifty pesetas they're here to-night,
speaker: Bill Gorton

qTextArr: ["I'll take it,", 'Good. You remember it, Jake. Fifty pesetas.']
qText: I'll take it, Good. You remember it, Jake. Fifty pesetas.

qText: I'll remember it myself,
speaker: Bill Gorton

qTextArr: ["It's a sure thing they'll come,", 'But maybe not to-night.']
qText: It's a sure thing they'll come, But maybe not to-night.
speaker: Jake Barnes

speaker: Robert Cohn

qTextArr: ['No. Why should I? Make it a hundred if you like.']
qText: No. Why should I? Make it a hundred if you like.
speaker: Bill Gorton

qText: All right. I'll take that.
speaker: Robert Cohn

qTextArr: ["That's enough,", "Or you'll have to make a book and give me some\nof it."]

That's enough, Or you'll have to make a book and give me some

speaker: Jake Barnes

qTextArr: ["I'm satisfied,", "You'll probably win it back at\nbridge, anyway."]
qText:
I'm satisfied, You'll probably win it back at
bridge, anyway.
speaker: Robert Cohn

qText: You haven't got it yet,
speaker: Bill Gorton

qTextArr: ['Say,', 'have I got any chance on that bet?']
qText: Say, have I got any chance on that bet?
speaker: Bill Gorton

qText:
You've got a rotten chance. They've never been on time anywhere. If

qTextArr:
["That was rather good. Ashley, chap she got the title from, was a
sailor, you know. Ninth baronet. When he came home he wouldn't sleep in
a bed. Always made Brett sleep on the floor. Finally, when he got really
bad, he used to tell her he'd kill her. Always slept with a loaded
service revolver. Brett used to take the shells out when he'd gone to
sleep. She hasn't had an absolutely happy life. Brett. Damned shame,
too. She enjoys things so."]
